<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1163711970261">
<term>double-slit interference experiment</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163711970266">Young’s double-slit experiment, which shows the interference of waves</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1163712284810">
<term>electron microscopy</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163712272767">microscopy that uses electron waves to “see” fine details of nano-size objects</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1163712272772">
<term>Heisenberg uncertainty principle</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163711057547">sets the limits on precision in simultaneous measurements of momentum and position of a particle</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1163711057551">
<term>wave-particle duality</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163712273108">particles can behave as waves and radiation can behave as particles</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
